<p class="p">We used Pearson correlation coefficient to measure the correlation of SSM with precipitation and temperature in the corresponding periods. For the data series 
 <italic class="italic">x</italic>
 <sub class="sub">1</sub>,
 <italic class="italic">x</italic>
 <sub class="sub">2</sub>,⋯
 <italic class="italic">x</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">n</italic>
 </sub> and 
 <italic class="italic">y</italic>
 <sub class="sub">1</sub>,
 <italic class="italic">y</italic>
 <sub class="sub">2</sub>,⋯
 <italic class="italic">y</italic>
 <sub class="sub">
  <italic class="italic">n</italic>
 </sub> of the two variables 
 <italic class="italic">X</italic> and 
 <italic class="italic">Y</italic>, the formula is as follows[
 <xref rid="pone.0217020.ref044" ref-type="bibr" class="xref">44</xref>]: 
 <disp-formula id="pone.0217020.e006" class="disp-formula">
  <alternatives class="alternatives">
   <graphic xlink:href="pone.0217020.e006.jpg" id="pone.0217020.e006g" mimetype="image" position="anchor" orientation="portrait" class="graphic" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"/>
   <math id="M6" class="math">
    <mi class="mi">R</mi>
    <mo class="mo">=</mo>
    <mfrac class="mfrac">
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <mrow class="mrow">
       <msubsup class="msubsup">
        <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">∑</mo>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">i</mi>
         <mo class="mo">=</mo>
         <mn class="mn">1</mn>
        </mrow>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mi class="mi">n</mi>
        </mrow>
       </msubsup>
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <mo class="mo">(</mo>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <msub class="msub">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">i</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mover accent="true" class="mover">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo class="mo">¯</mo>
         </mover>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">)</mo>
        <mo class="mo">(</mo>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <msub class="msub">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">y</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">i</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <mover accent="true" class="mover">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">y</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mo class="mo">¯</mo>
         </mover>
        </mrow>
        <mo class="mo">)</mo>
       </mrow>
      </mrow>
     </mrow>
     <mrow class="mrow">
      <msqrt class="msqrt">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <msubsup class="msubsup">
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">∑</mo>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">i</mi>
          <mo class="mo">=</mo>
          <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         </mrow>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">n</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msubsup>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">x</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">i</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <msup class="msup">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mover accent="true" class="mover">
            <mrow class="mrow">
             <mi class="mi">x</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mo class="mo">¯</mo>
           </mover>
           <mo class="mo">)</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mn class="mn">2</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msup>
        </mrow>
       </mrow>
      </msqrt>
      <msqrt class="msqrt">
       <mrow class="mrow">
        <msubsup class="msubsup">
         <mo stretchy="false" class="mo">∑</mo>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">i</mi>
          <mo class="mo">=</mo>
          <mn class="mn">1</mn>
         </mrow>
         <mrow class="mrow">
          <mi class="mi">n</mi>
         </mrow>
        </msubsup>
        <mrow class="mrow">
         <mo class="mo">(</mo>
         <msub class="msub">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">y</mi>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mi class="mi">i</mi>
          </mrow>
         </msub>
         <mo class="mo">−</mo>
         <msup class="msup">
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mover accent="true" class="mover">
            <mrow class="mrow">
             <mi class="mi">y</mi>
            </mrow>
            <mo class="mo">¯</mo>
           </mover>
           <mo class="mo">)</mo>
          </mrow>
          <mrow class="mrow">
           <mn class="mn">2</mn>
          </mrow>
         </msup>
        </mrow>
       </mrow>
      </msqrt>
     </mrow>
    </mfrac>
   </math>
  </alternatives>
  <label class="label">(6)</label>
 </disp-formula> the range of the correlation coefficient is [–1, 1]. If 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic> &gt; 0, the two variables are positively correlated; if 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic> = 0, the two variables are independent and have no correlation; if 
 <italic class="italic">R</italic> &lt; 0, it means the two variables are negatively correlated.
</p>
